								class Attribute2
								{
									property="ModuleCreateDiaryRecord_F_Description";
									expression="_this setVariable ['Description',_value,true];";
									class Value
									{
										class data
										{
											singleType="STRING";
											value="Two years ago, the Chernarussian Movement of the Red Star, or “ChDKZ” were designated as a terrorist group by the Chernarussian government. This led to an uprising in anti-government protests and riots which became widespread in the northern region of Chernarus.<br/><br/>     " \n " " \n "However, local law enforcement officers have managed to quell the unrest that have flooded the streets. After the quelling of the unrest, another paramilitary wing, the National Party, or “NAPA”, rose up in defiance of the spreading pro-Russian sentiment in Chernarus, vandalising, looting and destroying businesses with supposed ties to the ChDKZ. Four months ago, the ChDKZ surprised the Chernarussian government by rising in force, using weapons and military vehicles supplied by the Russian Federation; and besieged Chernarus. However, these uprisings were short, as the ChDKZ were led by inept military commanders, which led to a quick defeat for the ChDKZ.<br/><br/>     " \n "     " \n "In the early hours of this morning, the ChDKZ forces performed a surprise direct military action in Zelenogorsk, its military base and Green Mountain. Taking over all three locations and routing the stationed Chernarussian Defence Force and a token USMC squad in MB Zelenogorsk. " \n "";
										};
									};
								};
